import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['x'], bins=50, color='green')
    plt.axvline(data['x'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Mean: {data['x'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of x?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.hist(data['y'], bins=20, color='green')
    ax.axvline(data['y'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f'median={data["y"].median():.2f}')
    ax.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of y?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.hist(data['lumosity'], density=True, alpha=0.5, color='blue')
    ax.set_xlabel('Lumosity')
    ax.set_ylabel('Density')
    ax.axvline(data['lumosity'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['lumosity'].median()))
    plt.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of lumosity?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    color_counts = data['color'].value_counts()
    chart = color_counts.plot(kind='bar')
    chart.set_xlabel('Color')
    chart.set_ylabel('Count')
    chart.axhline(color_counts.max(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Max Count: {color_counts.max():.2f}')
    chart.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of colors used in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
